task.summary: Removed truly stupid static cacheing of itself thereby fixing the truly stupid bug that this caused!

For some reason I tried to get the top level project before copying project name to config when name is not set in config. I have no idea why I got the idea to do this in the first place. It is a strange thing to do and it doesn't make sense since it would (and did!) produce different names depending on where you start building!
Fixed an error in an example.
Added files with extension dtd as being of comment type html-xml.
Added files with extension dtd as being of comment type html-xml.

- APT and Markdown generated docs now links to license text on the web instead of linking to downloaded files. - Maven plugin now collects complete license information by saving to disk inbetween plugin invocations since static field does not work due to maven creating a new ClassLoaader per plugin invocation. - No longer tries to best-effort-fake a library license when there are errors in the library definition. It will now fail the build in this case. - For both auto collected license in formation and license information specified in pom, CLM will now complement it with URL if such is not specified but available in license library. - Added license url for all licenses in library. - Added OSGi Specification License 2.0 to library. - A bit of internal cosmetics. - Bumped version to 2.1.
Setup for deploy upload to maven.natusoft.se.
Ran CLM apply on all sources to update source headers with current version.
Damn it! Forgot to update README.md file.
- Greatly improved the HTML to markdown converter. Does a pretty good job for license texts at least. - Made already made markdown versions of several licenses available.
